History Tracers is a free and open-source teaching tool that supports both
students and teachers in the learning process by providing diverse tools for
history, genealogy, and interdisciplinary research.

It combines a built-in web server with a native desktop interface for browsing
interactive educational content, family trees, historical timelines, and more.
Available in English, Portuguese, and Spanish with support for 16 calendar
systems including Gregorian, Julian, Hebrew, Islamic, Chinese, and Mapuche.

Features:
  - Interactive history and genealogy content
  - Multi-language support (en-US, pt-BR, es-ES)
  - 16 calendar systems with date conversion
  - Family tree visualization with GEDCOM export
  - Built-in HTTP server with modern web interface
  - Publisher tool for content management and validation

WWW: https://github.com/historytracers/historytracers
